I'm mostly following the tutorial for "Course list viewer role", a variation on scenario 4 where I want to limit what students can see to only a few limited categories (even a single one) https://docs.moodle.org/311/en/Course_list_viewer_role I removed capability moodle/category:viewcourselist from the authenticated user role I created a new role with this capability for the category context Now let's say I have a hierarchy of categories : category1 category1.1 category2 If I assign a student this new role in category1, it works - student only sees courses from category1 and subcategory. If I assign a student this new role in subcategory category1.1, the student gets the cannotviewcategory error when accessing the category index (under /courses/). Notice the student can still access the subcategory with its id in URL (e.g. /courses/index.php?categoryid=10). I dive into the code, specically core_course_category#user_top() which "Returns the top-most category for the current user" and I found this cryptic comment at the end, when no top category is found : 
```text
       // User can not access any categories on the top level.


       // TODO 
MDL-10965
 find ANY/ALL categories in the tree where user has access to.


       return self::get(0, IGNORE_MISSING);
```
 https://github.com/moodle/moodle/blob/master/course/classes/category.php#L329 So this means this use case is not yet implemented ? But MDL-10965 is closed (maybe I should have posted this in the developer forum)

Hello, I respond to myself We finally implemented an SQL trigger to assign role automatically First get SQL tools SQL in order tu push the trigger to mysql http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/gui-tools/5.0.html Then push the following trigger (in our case based on attribute department,description and idnumber from user profile ldap fetch values) that will assign 3 role based on ldap value at each new user login in . 
```text
delimiter |
DROP TRIGGER assign_role|
CREATE TRIGGER assign_role AFTER INSERT ON mdl_user FOR EACH ROW BEGIN
DECLARE id_role1 bigint(10);
DECLARE id_role2 bigint(10);
DECLARE id_role3 bigint(10);
SELECT id INTO id_role1 FROM mdl_role WHERE shortname = NEW.department;
INSERT INTO mdl_role_assignments (roleid, contextid, userid, hidden, timestart, timeend, timemodified, modifierid, enrol, sortorder ) VALUES ( id_role1, 1, NEW.id, 0, NEW.timemodified, 0, NEW.timemodified, 2, "manual", 0);
SELECT id INTO id_role2 FROM mdl_role WHERE shortname = NEW.description;
INSERT INTO mdl_role_assignments (roleid, contextid, userid, hidden, timestart, timeend, timemodified, modifierid, enrol, sortorder ) VALUES ( id_role2, 1, NEW.id, 0, NEW.timemodified, 0, NEW.timemodified, 2, "manual", 0);
SELECT id INTO id_role3 FROM mdl_role WHERE shortname = NEW.idnumber;
INSERT INTO mdl_role_assignments (roleid, contextid, userid, hidden, timestart, timeend, timemodified, modifierid, enrol, sortorder ) VALUES ( id_role3, 1, NEW.id, 0, NEW.timemodified, 0, NEW.timemodified, 2, "manual", 0);
END;|
```
